de.upb.t2t.model

Class CurrencyCharacter

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.upb.t2t.model.CurrencyCharacter

  • public class CurrencyCharacter
extends java.lang.Object
    A rather static class that contains a list of all currency characters that have been parsed from the database on startup. A CurrencyCharacter consists of the actual char primitive (e.g. '$', '€', '£', ...), a singular and a plural form. The latter can be used for querying the database as look up Strings.
    Author:
    Michel May (michel-may@gmx.de)
